transcript:
these are three signs that you might
have high functioning anxiety number one
perfectionism people with high
functioning anxiety often hold
themselves to impossibly high standards
and feel intense pressure to meet those
standards and then when they don't meet
those standards they become very
self-critical number two overthinking
people with high function anxiety can
struggle with constant worrying
ruminating and analyzing everything in
their lives and then they usually spend
a lot of time trying to anticipate every
possible outcome of a situation which
then leads to overwhelm and exhaustion
number three difficulty relaxing even
when they have free time people with
high function anxiety often struggle to
relax and unwind and then they feel
guilty for taking time off because they
feel like they should be doing something
productive instead of resting which one
of these can you relate to
